summary: Sometimes, people ask my why Vision’s my favourite. I’m immensely fond of several MCU characters. Steve, Bucky, Wanda, Sam, and...
caption:
Sometimes, people ask my why Vision’s my favourite. I’m immensely fond of several MCU characters. Steve, Bucky, Wanda, Sam, and Thor are all up there with Vision. T’Challa, Gamora, Groot, Rocket, Jane, Peggy, and Loki for seconds. But Vision’s my all time favourite because he has the story and character arc that intrigues me the most. 

You have this immensely powerful person, who’s come into the world unconventionally and feels somewhat separated from other people, but is trying to understand humanity. And he does that ultimately by doing two very human things: failing, and falling in love. And I think that’s beautiful.

title: The Other Knew
body:
I love how in the stinger for Avengers (2012), the Other pretty much told Thanos, “Dude, if you invade Earth, you’re courting death.” And Thanos just smirks like, “Well, hell yes!”

I could only think how that scene gives a shout-out to the real reason Thanos even thinks about destroying Earth and other places is because that he has a thing for Death, as in a female persona of all things dark, lifeless and gloomy. Of course, the MCU couldn’t really use that reason since Death is Deadpool’s lover in the comics and rights and whatnot. But it’s nice to think that they put those lines in there because they have magical powers of knowing that six years later Avengers: Infinity War was coming out and wanted to put some jab as to why Thanos is nutsy coo-coo about destroying the universe.

Because the Other gave him bad relationship advice.

Just a thought… 😆😆😆
